{
  "date": "2026-03-26",
  "title": "Two Masters. One Choice.",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "Matthew 6:24",
      "text": "No one can serve two masters…. You cannot serve both God and money."
    },
    {
      "ref": "1 Timothy 6:10",
      "text": "For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil…."
    },
    {
      "ref": "Luke 6:38",
      "text": "Give, and it will be given to you…."
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It’s not a behavior issue."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It’s a heart issue."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You don’t drift because you’re weak."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You drift because something else has your loyalty."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Jesus didn’t say you might struggle with two masters."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "He said it’s impossible."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Something is forming you."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Something is leading you."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Something is owning your decisions."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And whatever has your heart…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "will eventually have your life."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Most men try to fix outcomes."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "More discipline."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "More effort."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "More control."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But Jesus goes deeper."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He doesn’t correct behavior first."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "He exposes allegiance."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“You cannot serve two masters….”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not “should not.”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not “try not to.”"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Cannot."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because your heart was never built to be divided."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "So when your life feels pulled in two directions…."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "God vs comfort",
            "Purpose vs pleasure",
            "Calling vs control"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "That tension isn’t random."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s revealing."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_real_issue",
      "label": "The Real Issue",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "1 Timothy 6:10 doesn’t say money is the problem."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It says the love of it is."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because money isn’t just currency."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s control."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s security."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s identity for many men."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And when your heart attaches to what feels safe…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "you will slowly detach from what requires trust."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "That’s how drift happens."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not overnight."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Through quiet re-alignment of the heart."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_hidden_war",
      "label": "The Hidden War",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Here’s what most men miss:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You can say you trust God…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "and still structure your life around something else."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Your calendar reveals it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Your stress reveals it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Your decisions reveal it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because your heart doesn’t follow your words."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It follows your treasure."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Jesus said it plainly (earlier in the same chapter):"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "So the question isn’t:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“Do I believe in God?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The question is:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“What is my heart actually anchored to?”"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_kingdom_flip",
      "label": "The Kingdom Flip",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Then comes Luke 6:38:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Give, and it will be given to you….”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This isn’t about transactions."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It’s about transformation."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because giving does something powerful:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It breaks the grip of whatever is trying to own your heart."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Every time you give…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "your heart loosens from control"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "and leans back into trust."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "That’s why generosity isn’t optional in the Kingdom."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s warfare."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_truth",
      "label": "The Truth",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You don’t accidentally serve God."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And you don’t accidentally serve money."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Both are chosen."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Repeatedly."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Daily."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And here’s the uncomfortable reality:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Your habits are revealing your master."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not your intentions."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not your beliefs."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Your patterns."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Stop trying to manage behavior."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Start examining allegiance."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because once your heart is aligned…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "your life will follow."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But if your heart stays divided…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "no amount of effort will create peace."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Where is my heart actually anchored right now?",
            "What am I trusting more than God…. even if I wouldn’t say it out loud?",
            "What do my spending, schedule, and stress reveal about my true master?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "My heart belongs to God alone."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will not be mastered by money, comfort, or control."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I choose trust over security."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I choose surrender over self-protection."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And I align my life with what lasts."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Today, practice intentional release:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Give something that costs you"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Time, money, attention, or control"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Without hesitation"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not to prove anything."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "But to retrain your heart."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because every act of giving…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "is a vote for who your master is."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "“Whatever has your heart…. will eventually have your life.” -TheWrkShop"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-03-26_matthew-6-24_two-masters-one-choice|"
}
